Techland has announced that Dying Light 2 has been delayed to February 4 2022. The open-world zombie adventure was previously scheduled to launch on PlayStation 5, PlayStation 4, Xbox Series X/S, Xbox One, and PC on December 7. 

Swipe to read the full statement released by Techland 👉

node.text:
Marvel's Spider-Man 2 is going to knock our socks off, according to the actor who is playing Venom 👇

Insomniac Games had left a trail of breadcrumbs hinting that Venom would be on his way to the world in some shape or form, and it's actor Tony Todd who is voicing the villain. The actor has actually been attached to Marvel's Spider-Man 2 for about two months now and has thanked fans for their enthusiasm for his latest role. 

Tony Todd 🗣️ "As an actual gamer [I] couldn't be more thrilled," said Todd in a reply to a Tweet from Gears of War creator Cliff Bleszinski. He also added that the sequel is "massive" and that's why we won't see it on the shelves until 2023 at the earliest.

node.text:
We're still a pretty long way away from this new Indie adventure seeing the light of day. However, it does look as if this whip-cracking romp will be yet another Xbox console exclusive... 💚

Bethesda got scooped up by Microsoft last year, and a number of big releases that might previously have been multiplatform have since been confirmed as Xbox exclusives. According to reliable Xbox insider Shpeshal Nick, it won't be. 

Revealing the information on Twitter, he confirmed he'd go into more detail on the game's exclusivity as part of an upcoming episode of his Rumour Mill podcast.

Swipe to watch the teaser trailer 👉

node.text:
Marvel has dropped the first trailer for the upcoming Hawkeye Disney Plus series, and it's... much more festive than we were expecting... 🎄

"This holiday season, the best gifts come with a bow," Disney teased on social media. Hawkeye arrives on the Disney Plus streaming service November 24, and will air in six weekly instalments - which should take us right up to Christmas! Click the link in bio to watch the trailer 🔗
